# E2E Verification

Use automated checks before reporting UI/canvas/online work as done.

## Commands

| Command | When |
|---------|------|
| `npm run test:unit` | Logic/model changes only |
| `npm run test:e2e` | UI, canvas, routing, Firebase online flows |
| `npm run verify` | Full agent check: format + unit + e2e + build |

## Selectors

Prefer stable `data-testid` attributes:

- `enter-local`, `enter-online` — home mode cards
- `mode-move`, `mode-draw`, `mode-erase` — toolbar modes
- `clear-all`, `load-image` — toolbar actions
- `canvas-stage` — Konva canvas wrapper

Reuse helpers in `e2e/helpers.ts` (`goToLocalMode`, `drawStrokeOnCanvas`, etc.).

## Online tests

E2E starts Firebase Emulator automatically via `npm run e2e:server` (Playwright `webServer`), or reuses a healthy dev server on port 3000.

Online rooms are created through the Emulator REST API (`e2e/helpers.ts`) for stable, headless setup. Home-card click flows are covered indirectly via `/local` navigation and API room creation.

First-time setup in Dev Container:

```bash
npm run test:e2e:install
sudo env "PATH=$PATH" npx playwright install-deps chromium
```

## Failure artifacts

On failure, inspect:

- `playwright-report/index.html` — HTML report
- `test-results/` — screenshots and traces

## Scope guidance

- Canvas drawing: verify mode switch + stroke via `canvasHasRedStroke`
- Online room: use `enter-online` (creates room via Emulator), not production Firebase
- Do not rely on browser MCP alone when `npm run test:e2e` can cover the flow
